  <titles>
    <title type="display">Taking Care of Small Business Tax Simplification Act of 2005</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to allow the subchapter S election to be made on a return filed before the due date with extensions, to reduce the payroll deposit penalties for failures to make deposits in the prescribed manner, and to allow a married couple who operates a unincorporated business as co-owners to file separate self-employment tax returns.</title>
